yle="clear: both;"></div></div></div><div id="offerings-dropdown"><a href="consult.php"><div class="dropdown-item">CONSULT</div></a><a href="design.php"><div class="dropdown-item">DESIGN</div></a><a href="build.php"><div class="dropdown-item">BUILD</div></a><a href="maintain.php"><div class="dropdown-item">MAINTAIN</div></a></div><div id="nav-menu"><div id="menu-btn"><div id="header15">Menu</div><div id="header16"><img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhQABAAIAAAMXFxQAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAABAAEAAAAJFhI+py+0Po5y02ouz3rz7D4biSJbmiabqyrbuC8fyTNf2jef6zvf+DwwKh8Si8YhMKpfMpvMJjUqn1Kr1is1qt9yuF1AAADs=" lazyload="images/hamburger.png" style="width: 100%; height: auto;"></div></div><div id="mobile-nav"><a href="index.php"><div id="header18">HOME</div></a><a href="ourstory.php"><div id="header19">OUR STORY<br></div></a><a href="offerings.php"><div id="header20">OFFERINGS</div></a><a href="contact.php"><div id="header21">REQUEST A CONSULTATION<br></div></a></div></div></div></div><div id="i23"><div class="fadeInBottomInactive">Our Story<br></div></div><div id="i25"><div id="i26">Our story contains more than 40 years of experience in bringing our clients’ ideas to life. We are an African American- and veteran-owned licensed general contractor headquartered in Rancho Cucamonga, California. We can build anything you want. We specialize in building accessory dwelling units (also known as ADUs), innovative workspaces, restaurants, and home remodeling projects. <br></div><div id="i27">Our Leadership Team<br></div><div id="i28"><div id="i29"><div class="team-avatar"><div id="i31">PC <br></div></div><div id="i32">Paul "Black Bear" Conor<br></div><div id="i33">President / Co-Founder<br></div></div><div id="i34"><div class="team-avatar"><div id="i36">DC<br></div></div><div id="i37">David Conor<br></div><div id="i38">Vice President / Co-Founder<br></div></div><div id="i39"><div class="team-avatar"><div id="i41">VF<br></div></div><div id="i42">Vincent Furriel, Jr.<br></div><div id="i43">RMO</div></div></div></div><div id="profile-wrapper"><div class="profile-bio"><div id="profile-wrapper1">✕ <br></div><div id="profile-wrapper2"><div id="profile-wrapper3"><img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhQABAAIAAAMXFxQAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAABAAEAAAAJFhI+py+0Po5y02ouz3rz7D4biSJbmiabqyrbuC8fyTNf2jef6zvf+DwwKh8Si8YhMKpfMpvMJjUqn1Kr1is1qt9yuF1AAADs=" lazyload="images/paul-edward.jpg" style="width: 100%; height: auto;"></div><div id="profile-wrapper4">Paul "Black Bear" Conor<br></div><div id="profile-wrapper5">President / Co-Founder<br></div><div id="profile-wrapper6">Paul “Black Bear” Conor is the president and one of the co-founders of Conor Construction and Development Corporation. Paul is a <u><a href="https://www.marines.mil/" target="_blank">US Marine Corps veteran</a></u> and successful entrepreneur. He grew up in South Central Los Angeles, attended the prestigious Harvard School for Boys (now known as <u><a href="https://www.hw.com" target="_blank">Harvard-Westlake</a></u>), and earned a Naval ROTC scholarship to the <u><a href="https://www.usc.edu/" target="_blank">University of Southern California</a></u>, where he earned his bachelor’s degree and commission as a US Marine Corps infantry officer. He is deeply committed to helping veterans and underdogs become successful in life. He brings more than 25 years of business management, consulting, and customer service experience to the company. <br></div></div></div><div class="profile-bio"><div id="profile-wrapper8">✕ <br></div><div id="profile-wrapper9"><div id="profile-wrapper10"><img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhQABAAIAAAMXFxQAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAABAAEAAAAJFhI+py+0Po5y02ouz3rz7D4biSJbmiabqyrbuC8fyTNf2jef6zvf+DwwKh8Si8YhMKpfMpvMJjUqn1Kr1is1qt9yuF1AAADs=" lazyload="images/AdobeStock_296386410-c.jpg" style="width: 100%; height: auto;"></div><div id="profile-wrapper11">David Conor<br></div><div id="profile-wrapper12">Vice President / Co-Founder<br></div><div id="profile-wrapper13">David Conor is a vice president and one of the co-founders of Conor Construction and Development Corporation. David has experience in construction project management, marketing, and operations. He grew up in Seattle, Washington and graduated from Azusa Pacific and Liberty Universities, where he earned his bachelor’s degree in business management. <br></div></div></div><div class="profile-bio"><div id="profile-wrapper15">✕ <br></div><div id="profile-wrapper16"><div id="profile-wrapper17">Vincent Furriel, Jr.<br></div><div id="profile-wrapper18">RMO</div><div id="profile-wrapper19">Vincent Furriel, Jr., is the responsible managing officer (RMO) for Conor Construction and Development Corporation. Vince is a <u><a href="https://www.marines.mil/" target="_blank">US Marine Corps veteran</a></u> and experienced general contractor, independent adjuster, and damage consultant. Before obtaining his General Contractor’s license, Vince has worked for some of the industry’s top builders, including <u><a href="https://yorkbuilders.com/" target="_blank">York Builders</a></u>, <u><a href="https://www.sshomes.net/" target="_blank">SS Homes</a></u>, <u><a href="https://www.drhorton.com/" target="_blank">D.R. Horton</a></u>, <u><a href="https://www.irvinecompany.com/" target="_blank">the Irvine Company</a></u>, <u><a href="https://goblusky.com/?gclid=Cj0KCQiAlsv_BRDtARIsAHMGVSZrq5IoNS7B5MC6MyYwTs0D1HOZMWXejDyP-FJJ7tKYdqiJGM7mrTAaApzlEALw_wcB" target="_blank">Har-Bro</a></u>, <u><a href="https://www.sheahomes.com/" target="_blank">Shea Homes</a></u>, and <u><a href="https://www.taylormorrison.com/" target="_blank">Lyon Homes</a></u>. He grew up in Southern California and was educated by the US Military Academy in California and the United States Marine Corps. Vince holds General Contractor and other construction licenses in California, Arizona, and Nevada.</div></div></div></div><div id="newfooter"><div id="newfooter0"><div id="newfooter1"><div id="newfooter2"><img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhQABAAIAAAMXFxQAA